/ Returns the adjusted label, or null if it should be skipped. /

onlyTopHalf



if true, draws only top half of the palette and labels stretched to whole window /




storage



will sometimes be used as storage for the return value. Don't read storage directly after the call. You can pass any string, it'll be cleared. const char* getAdjustedLabelText_( std::size_t labelIndex, bool onlyTopHalf, std::string& storage ) const;



/ Computes the max label pixel width. float getMaxLabelWidth_( bool onlyTopHalf = false ) const;
